12 0 obj
<< /Length 2375 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Type 2 Diabetes) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (What Is Type 2 Diabetes?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (In Type 2 diabetes, your body either does not produce enough insulin or your cells have) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (become resistant to insulin's effects. This results in elevated blood glucose \(sugar\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (levels that, over time, can damage blood vessels, nerves, and organs.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 600.4 Td (Key Terms to Know) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Insulin: Hormone that allows glucose to enter cells for energy) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Insulin resistance: Cells don't respond properly to insulin) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Glucose: Sugar in your blood \(from food and liver\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542.4 Td (- A1C: Average blood sugar over 2-3 months) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 528.4 Td (- Fasting glucose: Blood sugar after 8+ hours without food) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 514.4 Td (- Postprandial: Blood sugar after eating) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 484.6 Td (Blood Sugar Targets) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 462.6 Td (General Guidelines \(discuss with your doctor\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 446.6 Td (- Fasting \(before meals\): 80-130 mg/dL) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 432.6 Td (- 2 hours after meal start: Less than 180 mg/dL) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 418.6 Td (- A1C goal: Less than 7% \(or as set by your doctor\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 404.6 Td (- Bedtime: 100-140 mg/dL) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 374.8 Td (Risk Factors for Complications) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 356.8 Td (- Consistently elevated blood sugar) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 342.8 Td (- High blood pressure) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 328.8 Td (- High cholesterol) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 314.8 Td (- Smoking) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 300.8 Td (- Physical inactivity) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 286.8 Td (- Excess weight) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 257.0 Td (Potential Complications \(Prevention Is Key\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 239.0 Td (- Heart disease and stroke) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 225.0 Td (- Nerve damage \(neuropathy\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 211.0 Td (- Kidney disease \(nephropathy\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 197.0 Td (- Eye damage \(retinopathy\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 183.0 Td (- Foot problems and slow healing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 169.0 Td (These complications are largely preventable with good blood sugar control!) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
