106 0 obj
<< /Length 3093 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: Can Type 2 diabetes be reversed?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (Many people achieve remission \(normal blood sugar without medication\) through significant) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (lifestyle changes, especially weight loss and low-carb eating. Discuss realistic goals) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632.2 Td (with your doctor.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 604.4 Td (Q: How often should I check my blood sugar?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (This depends on your treatment plan. Those on insulin may test 4+ times daily. Others may) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (test fasting and after meals a few times per week. Follow your doctor's guidance.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 546.6 Td (Q: Are all carbs bad?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.6 Td (No. Focus on quality: whole grains, legumes, fruits, and vegetables are healthful.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 516.6 Td (Minimize refined carbs, sugar, and processed foods. Portion control matters most.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 488.8 Td (Q: Can I still eat fruit?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472.8 Td (Yes! Choose whole fruits over juice. Berries, apples, and citrus have lower glycemic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 458.8 Td (impact. Pair fruit with protein or fat to slow glucose absorption.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 431.0 Td (Q: What about artificial sweeteners?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 415.0 Td (They don't raise blood sugar directly, but may affect gut bacteria and appetite. Use in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 401.0 Td (moderation. Water, unsweetened tea, and sparkling water are best.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 373.2 Td (Q: Should I follow a keto diet?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 357.2 Td (Very low-carb diets can significantly improve blood sugar but must be medically) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 343.2 Td (supervised, especially if on insulin or sulfonylureas \(risk of hypoglycemia\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 329.2 Td (Sustainability matters.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 301.4 Td (Q: How does sleep affect blood sugar?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 285.4 Td (Poor sleep increases insulin resistance, raises cortisol, and makes blood sugar harder to) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271.4 Td (control. Prioritize 7-9 hours of quality sleep.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 243.6 Td (Q: Can stress raise my blood sugar?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 227.6 Td (Yes, significantly. Stress hormones \(cortisol, adrenaline\) tell the liver to release) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 213.6 Td (glucose. Chronic stress can raise A1C by 0.5-1%.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 185.8 Td (Q: When should I call my doctor?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 169.8 Td (Contact your doctor if blood sugar is consistently over 250, under 70, if you feel sick,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 155.8 Td (or if you notice signs of complications \(numbness, vision changes, slow healing\).) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 128.0 Td (Q: Will I need insulin eventually?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 112.0 Td (Not necessarily. Many people manage Type 2 with lifestyle and oral medications long-term.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 98.0 Td (Needing insulin isn't a failure - it means your body needs additional support.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
